profile_positions.description:
As Senior Consultant it was my responsibility to lead and conduct economic and strategic analysis, such as economic impact analysis in merger and state aid cases, commercial due diligence as well as strategic market and customer analysis. I also took on responsibility beyond my role and became lead advisor to an international client in one of my team’s largest assignment.

Assignments included, amongst others, the following:
-	Starting out with being a supporting economist, I was asked to become lead advisor to an Irish local authority in a complex state aid investigation by the European Commission (EC) regarding a waste-to-energy facility in Ireland. I assisted by managing communication with the EC, writing response documents to the EC, conducting economic and financial analysis as well as facilitating in negotiations with the aid recipient on amendments to the project agreement. In result, the aid was approved by the EC and the project allowed to be realised; 
-	An economic analysis of a Dutch hospital merger with the purpose to show that it would not substantially reduce competition between the hospitals . Result: the merger was approved by the Dutch competition authority; and
-	A review of a guarantee scheme by the Dutch Ministry to small- and medium-sized enterprises for compliance with European state aid rules. Result: the scheme was approved by the EC; 

The analysis conducted by me was always perceived by colleagues and clients as being of high quality. Clients said that they liked my pro-active way of working and out-of-the box thinking to help them achieve the desired outcome.

I was responsible for economic and econometric analysis of competition and merger cases and assessments of regulatory models and decisions. Further, I was responsible for marketing by preparing and conducting seminars on competition economics for international law firms and preparing proposals.

Assignments included, amongst others:
-	Assessment of cartel effects and damages in cartel investigations before the EC and European national courts; 
-	Economic advice in an international litigation between two leading telecom operators; 
-	Economic market definition in an  acquisition on the European oil market; 
-	Supporting expert advice to a mobile operator in an appeals against regulatory decision by European regulators; and 
-	Assisting the Italian telecom regulator in a consultation on the margin squeeze test and guidelines.

My task was to conduct economic analysis and research in competition, merger, and regulation cases. Assignments included, amongst others:
-	Assisting a large telecoms company with the market definition and economic analysis of a merger on the optic fibre market in an investigation by the Dutch competition authority; 
-	Economic advice in disputes about regulation of telecom interconnection charges in Hong Kong; 
-	Economic assessment of regulatory disputes in telecom and energy markets before European national regulators; and research on cartel fines and the effectiveness of the EC’s Fining Guidelines.
